    "Of those that provided qualitative survey comments, 9 (40.9%) held leadership positions in the department, and 8 (36.4%) were women while the remaining 14 (63.6%) were men.",
    "The average time on faculty for these participants was 15.5 years (SD: 11.0 years).",
    "The surgeons that participated in the interviews were composed of 6 (54.5%) men and 5 (45.5%) women; the majority (n = 7, 63.6%) held leadership roles in the department, and the average time on faculty was 20.7 years (SD: 11.0 years).",
    "On average, participants indicated that just over 65% of their time is dedicated to clinical activities, with their remaining time being distributed across education (mean: 13.1%), research (mean: 9.4%), and administrative work (mean 12.4%).",
    "An overview of these characteristics is available in Table 2."
